schema.description: Artifacts of resources. Artifacts are unique (single-value) per resource and are used to store metadata that is too large or numerous to be stored directly on the resource. Since artifacts are stored separately from parent resources, they should generally be used for metadata that is needed infrequently, i.e. not for display in primary views of the resource but perhaps displayed or downloaded upon request. The ListArtifacts method allows artifacts to be quickly enumerated and checked for presence without downloading their (potentially-large) contents.

schema.description: An ApiSpec describes a version of an API in a structured way. ApiSpecs provide formal descriptions that consumers can use to use a version. ApiSpec resources are intended to be fully-resolved descriptions of an ApiVersion. When specs consist of multiple files, these should be bundled together (e.g. in a zip archive) and stored as a unit. Multiple specs can exist to provide representations in different API description formats. Synchronization of these representations would be provided by tooling and background services.

annotations.description: Annotations attach non-identifying metadata to resources. Annotation keys and values are less restricted than those of labels, but should be generally used for small values of broad interest. Larger, topic- specific metadata should be stored in Artifacts.

contents.description: The contents of the spec. Provided by API callers when specs are created or updated. To access the contents of a spec, use GetApiSpecContents.

create_time.description: Creation timestamp; when the spec resource was created.

filename.description: A possibly-hierarchical name used to refer to the spec from other specs.

hash.description: A SHA-256 hash of the spec's contents

labels.description: Labels attach identifying metadata to resources. Identifying metadata can be used to filter list operations. Label keys and values can be no longer than 64 characters (Unicode codepoints), can only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores and dashes. International characters are allowed. No more than 64 user labels can be associated with one resource (System labels are excluded). See https://goo.gl/xmQnxf for more information and examples of labels. System reserved label keys are prefixed with "registry.googleapis.com/" and cannot be changed.

mime_type.description: A style (format) descriptor for this spec that is specified as a Media Type (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Media_type). Possible values include "application/vnd.apigee.proto", "application/vnd.apigee.openapi", and "application/vnd.apigee.graphql", with possible suffixes representing compression types. These hypothetical names are defined in the vendor tree defined in RFC6838 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6838) and are not final.

revision_create_time.description: Revision creation timestamp; when the represented revision was created.

revision_id.description: The revision ID of the spec. A new revision is committed whenever the spec contents are changed. The format is an 8-character hexadecimal string.

revision_tags.description: The revision tags associated with this revision.

revision_update_time.description: Last update timestamp: when the represented revision was last modified.

size_bytes.description: The size of the spec file in bytes.

source_uri.description: The original source URI of the spec (if one exists). This is an external location that can be used for reference purposes but which may not be authoritative since this external resource may change after the spec is retrieved.

mappings.name: RollbackApiSpec sets the current revision to a specified prior revision. Note that this creates a new revision with a new revision ID.

schema.description: An ApiSpec describes a version of an API in a structured way. ApiSpecs provide formal descriptions that consumers can use to use a version. ApiSpec resources are intended to be fully-resolved descriptions of an ApiVersion. When specs consist of multiple files, these should be bundled together (e.g. in a zip archive) and stored as a unit. Multiple specs can exist to provide representations in different API description formats. Synchronization of these representations would be provided by tooling and background services.

annotations.description: Annotations attach non-identifying metadata to resources. Annotation keys and values are less restricted than those of labels, but should be generally used for small values of broad interest. Larger, topic- specific metadata should be stored in Artifacts.

contents.description: The contents of the spec. Provided by API callers when specs are created or updated. To access the contents of a spec, use GetApiSpecContents.

create_time.description: Creation timestamp; when the spec resource was created.

filename.description: A possibly-hierarchical name used to refer to the spec from other specs.

hash.description: A SHA-256 hash of the spec's contents

labels.description: Labels attach identifying metadata to resources. Identifying metadata can be used to filter list operations. Label keys and values can be no longer than 64 characters (Unicode codepoints), can only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores and dashes. International characters are allowed. No more than 64 user labels can be associated with one resource (System labels are excluded). See https://goo.gl/xmQnxf for more information and examples of labels. System reserved label keys are prefixed with "registry.googleapis.com/" and cannot be changed.

mime_type.description: A style (format) descriptor for this spec that is specified as a Media Type (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Media_type). Possible values include "application/vnd.apigee.proto", "application/vnd.apigee.openapi", and "application/vnd.apigee.graphql", with possible suffixes representing compression types. These hypothetical names are defined in the vendor tree defined in RFC6838 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6838) and are not final.

revision_create_time.description: Revision creation timestamp; when the represented revision was created.

revision_id.description: The revision ID of the spec. A new revision is committed whenever the spec contents are changed. The format is an 8-character hexadecimal string.

revision_tags.description: The revision tags associated with this revision.

revision_update_time.description: Last update timestamp: when the represented revision was last modified.

size_bytes.description: The size of the spec file in bytes.

source_uri.description: The original source URI of the spec (if one exists). This is an external location that can be used for reference purposes but which may not be authoritative since this external resource may change after the spec is retrieved.

mappings.name: GetApiSpec returns a specified spec.
